@ENDNODE


@NODE INTRODUCTION "Introduction"

	@{b}Introduction@{ub}

LeoUtilities is a collection of some small utilities made by @{"Leopold-Soft" link AUTHOR} to make everyone's life a bit easier and more fun.

All Amiga binaries are startable and usable only from the Shell, with the exception of @{"MemTest" link MEMTEST} which can also be started from the Workbench. They require at least OS 1.3 to work and some require OS 2.0 or/and a 68020 CPU. All programs are compiled to work with a standard 4K stack. All binaries are compiled with the SAS C developement system (ver. 6.51).

Some programs are written in standard ANSI C and can be compiled on any system that has an ANSI C compliant compiler. Some programs may need significant amounts of stack.
@ENDNODE




